As far as I know, yeah. I've tried to find something to make it go away, but nothing does, and I've tried a lot. Trannyism is a legitimate curse that there's usually no escape from. You either bottle it all in and deal with all of the mental health problems from severe untreated gender dysphoria and hope you don't snap when you're 50 with 3 kids and a wife and turn into a boomerhon but be treated more normally by society despite your nearly guaranteed soulless and robotic behavior from the struggles of repression eating you alive, or you roll the dice and transition and hope you pass enough and it helps your dysphoria enough for it to be worth it, and be reviled by a good chunk of everyone who knows just for trying, and maybe get some other new problems you never had before.
Both are shitty but the second option is looking way more appealing right about now, especially talking to some trans women who've said they're way happier now than before and it was totally worth any damage to their life, and seeing timelines of trans women who used to look a little like me end up looking like beautiful cis women and feeling hugely jealous and wanting it for myself.
>>28695491
